<div class="h4">Latest South African Schools News</div>
New Education Figures Released Pretoria, South Africa 2010: South Africa currently has over 12 million learners, some 386 600 teachers and approximately 26 000 schools, including 1 098 registered independent or privately owned schools. There are roughly 6 000 high schools (grade 7 to grade 12) in South Africa and 20 000 primary (grade 0 to grade 6) schools. Currently the ratio of scholars (known as "learners" in terms of the country's outcomes-based education system) to teachers ("educators") is 32.6 to one in government schools, while private schools generally have one teacher for every 17.5 scholars. If you would like to keep up to date with the latest Schools 4 South Africa news please subscribe to our newsletter.
      </div>
      <div class="row">
<div class="h4">Upcoming Services at Schools 4 South Africa</div>
We are constantly implementing new features and updating services in co-operation with the South African schools community. All parents and schools that have signed up for our Schools 4 South Africa services will be informed of any changes to the website via our quarterly newsletter and here on the site.
